			  },
			  "CustomInstructions": "This semantic model provides an end‑to‑end view of retail sales performance and customer purchasing behavior, combining basket‑level and item‑level facts with shared business dimensions for time, product, and store. It enables analysis of revenue, units sold, order behavior, and promotional effectiveness across regions, channels, categories, and brands.\nThe model supports both strategic KPIs (Orders, Revenue, AOV, promotion impact) and detailed drill‑downs (product, brand, and item‑level sales), making it suitable for executive reporting, operational monitoring, and AI‑driven self‑service insights through Copilot.\n\nDate intelligence is centralized in dim_date, providing standard calendar attributes (year, quarter, month, day, weekday) to ensure consistent time-based analysis.\nProduct context is modeled in dim_product, including category, brand, lifecycle status, and effective timestamps to support trend, assortment, and activation analysis.\nStore and channel context is captured in dim_store, enabling regional and channel-level performance comparisons.\nBasket-level behavior is represented in fact_basket_summary, supporting KPIs such as Orders, AOV, Promo Orders %, and Promo Users %, with clear separation of promotional and non-promotional activity.\nItem-level sales detail is modeled in fact_sales_item, enabling precise Revenue and Units Sold analysis by product, category, and brand."
			}
